+2. [MEDIUM] Fix 3 acceptance criteria weaken the verified cancel predicate вҖ” Step 3.2 uses `sessionOrders.filter((o) => !isCancelledOrder(o))` (prompt lines 884-890) so terminal visibility ignores both raw `'cancelled'` and `stageInfo.internal_code === 'cancel'`. The AC at lines 998-999 rewrites that as `sessionOrders.filter(o.status !== 'cancelled')`, which is narrower than the proposed code and contradicts the v6/v10 rationale carried through Fixes 1 and 3. PROMPT FIX: align the AC with `!isCancelledOrder(o)` or say "exclude cancelled orders via the same normalized predicate as Fix 1."
